Is there any specific reason that the systemName of first node must be "system"?

In Bletchley, we have host[1-6], and the systemName of host1 will become "system" instead of "system1".

Could it be something like this?
```
if (nodeStr.find("host0") != std::string::npos)
{
  // single host
  systemName = "system";
}
else
{
  // multi host
  systemName = "system" + computerSystemIndex;
}
```

Suggest some more defensive programming such as:

```
static constexpr std::string_view systemToken = "system";
static constexpr std::string zero = "0";

auto location = systemNameStr.rfind(systemTokenStr);
if (location == std::string::npos) return zero;

auto index = systemNameStr.substr(location + systemToken.length())
if (index.length() == 0) return zero;

return index;
```
